{
  "texts": [
    "Instruction Following in LLMs.",
    "Instruction following is a key capability of LLMs that has been extensively studied in recent years, including various approaches to evaluate and improve LLMs' ability to understand and execute human instructions.",
    "For instance, efforts in instruction tuning have shown that fine-tuning LLMs on carefully curated sets of instructions can significantly enhance their zero-shot performance on unseen instructions (Sanh et al., 2021; Wei et al., 2021; Chung et al., 2024).",
    "More recently, Reinforcement Learning from Human Feedback (RLHF; Christiano et al., 2017) has been employed to align LLMs more closely with user intent, leading to models that better adhere to instructions in practice (Stiennon et al., 2020; Ouyang et al., 2022).",
    "Parallel to these advancements, the evaluation of instruction-following capabilities has also seen significant progress."
  ]
}